        "content": "- Time = Distance / Speed\n- If a train of length L meters crosses:\n  • A pole: Time = L / Speed\n  • A platform of length P: Time = (L + P) / Speed\n  • Another train of length L₂: Time = (L + L₂) / Relative Speed\n\nSpeed is always converted to m/s using:\nSpeed (m/s) = (Speed in km/hr) × (5/18)"
