    "topic": "Practice Example 3",
    "subtopics": [
      {
        "subtopic": "Two Trains Moving Opposite",
        "content": "**Q:** Two trains of lengths 120 m and 130 m are moving in opposite directions at 60 km/hr and 90 km/hr. How long will they take to cross each other?\n**Solution:**\nRelative speed = (60 + 90) × 5/18 = 150 × 5/18 = 41.67 m/s\nTotal length = 120 + 130 = 250 m\nTime = 250 / 41.67 ≈ 6 seconds\n**Answer:** 6 seconds"
      }
